WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:03.168
[ <i>gunfire</i> ]

00:03.170 --> 00:04.470
Eddie:
<i>Everyone thought my pops</i>

00:04.472 --> 00:06.038
<i>Was the nicest guy in orlando.</i>
<i>[ chuckles ]</i>

00:06.040 --> 00:08.374
<i>But he had a guilty pleasure.</i>

00:08.376 --> 00:10.175
<i>He loved gangster movies --</i>

00:10.177 --> 00:12.945
<i>Immigrants fighting for their</i>
<i>piece of the american dream.</i>

00:12.947 --> 00:14.947
Eh, so many bullets.
[ chuckles ]

00:14.949 --> 00:17.149
<i>And deep down,</i>
<i>he was the same way.</i>

00:17.151 --> 00:19.618
<i>Because when it came</i>
<i>to providing for his family,</i>

00:19.620 --> 00:21.820
<i>He would do</i>
<i>whatever it took.</i>

00:21.822 --> 00:22.988
[ siren wailing ]

00:22.990 --> 00:25.624
[ both panting ]

00:25.626 --> 00:28.027
[ heart beating ]

00:31.731 --> 00:33.165
Aah! Whoa!

00:33.167 --> 00:34.133
But my shoe!

00:34.135 --> 00:36.035
Leave it!
Oh, no!

00:36.037 --> 00:38.637
Let me tell you something
about that shoe!

00:38.639 --> 00:40.806
Nordstroms hardly ever
has a sale.

00:40.808 --> 00:42.174
And one time,
by the grace of god --

00:42.176 --> 00:43.976
No time for a speech!
Ooh! Aah! No!

00:43.978 --> 00:45.511
My shoe!
Aah!

00:45.513 --> 00:47.713
-- Captions by vitac --

00:47.715 --> 00:48.914
♪ fresh off the boat

00:48.916 --> 00:50.716
♪ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ♪

00:50.718 --> 00:52.384
♪ if you don't know, homey,
now you know ♪

00:52.386 --> 00:53.719
♪ fresh off the boat

00:53.721 --> 00:56.722
♪ homey, you don't know
where I come from ♪

00:56.724 --> 00:57.923
♪ but I know where I'm goin'

00:57.925 --> 01:01.060
♪ I'm fresh off the boat

01:01.895 --> 01:03.662
<i>My dad was excited</i>
<i>to show us</i>

01:03.664 --> 01:05.197
<i>The newest promotion</i>
<i>for his restaurant.</i>

01:05.199 --> 01:07.533
<i>My mom, on the other hand,</i>
<i>was less enthused.</i>

01:07.535 --> 01:09.334
It's a sunny day
in orlando,

01:09.336 --> 01:11.103
You're driving
down the street --

01:11.105 --> 01:14.273
Well, I'm setting the scene,
building suspense

01:14.275 --> 01:15.707
For when you guys
see the restaurant billboard.

01:15.709 --> 01:16.708
Play along.

01:16.710 --> 01:18.077
"play"?
I don't like to play.

01:18.079 --> 01:21.046
Well, <i>you</i> don't,
but you are not you.

01:21.048 --> 01:22.848
No, you are a beefy
lake-house owner

01:22.850 --> 01:24.216
In town
for the sailing convention,

01:24.218 --> 01:26.051
And you are hungry.

01:26.053 --> 01:27.352
No, I'm not.
I just had grapes.

01:27.354 --> 01:28.420
Damn it!
[ sighs ]

01:28.422 --> 01:29.621
[ rapping ]
♪ I'm not the butler

01:29.623 --> 01:31.924
♪ I'll cut ya,
headbutt ya ♪

01:31.926 --> 01:34.526
Mom, eddie's rapping
at my always-there bear.

01:34.528 --> 01:35.961
Did they give you
that pin for narc-ing?

01:35.963 --> 01:37.696
No,
that's tattle-turtle.

01:37.698 --> 01:40.232
This is for the school's
best attendance record.

01:40.234 --> 01:42.234
Why is this billboard
so far away?

01:42.236 --> 01:43.769
You could have
put it here.

01:44.971 --> 01:47.739
Or here. Or here.

01:47.741 --> 01:49.308
Louis: Well,
those big companies

01:49.310 --> 01:51.543
Can afford to
put billboards anywhere.

01:51.545 --> 01:53.112
I have to be
more strategic.

01:53.114 --> 01:55.314
See?

01:55.316 --> 01:59.051
Now, this is the best billboard
spot in all of orlando.

01:59.053 --> 02:00.452
It's the longest
red light,

02:00.454 --> 02:03.155
There's no tall buildings
to block the view,

02:03.157 --> 02:06.458
And there's a homeless man
who's always on the corner,

02:06.460 --> 02:07.960
Reminding drivers
that they're hungry.

02:07.962 --> 02:10.395
Is that a bird
in his pocket?

02:10.397 --> 02:11.763
Yes. It's dead.

02:11.765 --> 02:14.566
So, naturally, you divert
your eyes away from him,

02:14.568 --> 02:17.469
You turn your head,
and you look up to see...

02:20.907 --> 02:22.908
Whoa, cool! Did you really
hold up that cow?!

02:22.910 --> 02:24.176
Yeah, I did.

02:24.178 --> 02:26.645
It was heavy, too.
He had just had lunch.

02:28.148 --> 02:30.349
[ school bell rings ]
<i>meanwhile,</i>
<i>I had my own problems,</i>

02:30.351 --> 02:31.583
<i>But they weren't at school.</i>

02:31.585 --> 02:33.085
<i>As tough as school was,</i>

02:33.087 --> 02:35.187
<i>It was a cakewalk</i>
<i>compared to the bus.</i>

02:35.189 --> 02:36.421
[ indistinct conversation ]

02:36.423 --> 02:37.923
♪ wild, wild west

02:37.925 --> 02:39.458
[ indistinct shouting ]

02:39.460 --> 02:40.826
♪ wild, wild west

02:40.828 --> 02:42.461
Boy: Got ya!
Boy #2: Oh-oh! No fair!

02:42.463 --> 02:43.996
♪ wild, wild west
<i>the bus was</i>
<i>the only part of the day</i>

02:43.998 --> 02:45.164
<i>Without adult supervision.</i>
<i>♪ wild, wild west </i>

02:45.166 --> 02:46.331
<i>So me and the other</i>
<i>sixth graders</i>

02:46.333 --> 02:47.866
<i>Were left</i>
<i>to fend for ourselves.</i>

02:47.868 --> 02:49.268
♪ wild, wild west
<i>if you wanted to survive,</i>

02:49.270 --> 02:50.969
<i>You had to stay up front</i>
<i>and pretend to sleep.</i>

02:50.971 --> 02:52.838
♪ wild, wild west
<i>if you didn't,</i>
<i>things could get ugly.</i>

02:52.840 --> 02:54.940
I just glad I got
to keep ol' bess here.

02:54.942 --> 02:57.142
My teachers usually
like to keep my projects,

02:57.144 --> 02:58.710
But that's not fair
to my parents.

02:58.712 --> 03:00.279
They fund my creations --
[ screams ]

03:00.281 --> 03:01.880
[ crunch! ]
oh, bess!

03:01.882 --> 03:03.549
[ clatter ]

03:03.551 --> 03:04.550
Fool.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.151
Better him than us.

03:06.153 --> 03:07.719
<i>Sure, the driver was there,</i>

03:07.721 --> 03:10.155
<i>But he wasn't</i>
<i>paid enough to care.</i>

03:10.157 --> 03:11.523
[ sighs ]
lucky hands.

03:11.525 --> 03:13.358
Lucky hands.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.694
<i>The only bright spot</i>
<i>on the daily hell ride</i>

03:15.696 --> 03:16.862
<i>Was my neighbor nicole.</i>

03:16.864 --> 03:18.664
<i>She was as tough</i>
<i>as a stale tootsie roll,</i>

03:18.666 --> 03:21.033
<i>And I loved it.</i>
<i>[ sighs ]</i>

03:21.035 --> 03:23.302
Hey.

03:23.304 --> 03:25.504
[ shouting continues ]

03:25.506 --> 03:28.507
[ laughter ]
♪ wild, wild west

03:28.509 --> 03:31.143
What are you looking at?
♪ wild, wild west

03:31.145 --> 03:33.312
♪ wild, wild west

03:33.314 --> 03:36.114
I'll get this to his mother.
♪ wild, wild west

03:36.849 --> 03:40.219
One bloomin' onion.

03:40.221 --> 03:43.388
Uh, mitch,
I think you meant to say

03:43.390 --> 03:45.190
<i>Booming</i> onion.
[ chuckles ]

03:45.192 --> 03:47.392
"blooming onion"
is the intellectual property

03:47.394 --> 03:49.394
Of another,
less-good restaurant, okay?

03:49.396 --> 03:50.829
Right.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.197
Like
they have potato skins,

03:52.199 --> 03:54.032
But we have
tomato skins.

03:54.034 --> 03:55.200
Nope. No, no.

03:55.202 --> 03:56.368
No,
none of your ideas --

03:56.370 --> 03:59.004
No tomato skins,
no jalapeño toppers,

03:59.006 --> 04:00.539
And no buffalo things.

04:00.541 --> 04:02.407
You know,
I don't have to take this.

04:02.409 --> 04:05.210
I get job offers all the time
from other restaurants.

04:05.212 --> 04:08.747
There's heat on mitch.
Oh, yeah.

04:09.716 --> 04:11.850
Louis, you were right
about the billboard.

04:11.852 --> 04:14.720
I told you. The place
has been packed all day.

04:14.722 --> 04:16.722
People have been coming up to me
and talking to me about it.

04:16.724 --> 04:20.125
Hmm.
One lady even let me
cut in front of her in line

04:20.127 --> 04:21.693
At the grocery store.

04:21.695 --> 04:24.296
Wow, you usually get into fights
at the grocery store.

04:24.298 --> 04:25.297
I know!
[ chuckles ]

04:25.299 --> 04:26.565
And we have been invited

04:26.567 --> 04:29.434
To the chamber of commerce
charity-fundraising event.

04:29.436 --> 04:30.435
Hmm.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.971
It's at a country club!
[ gasps ]

04:32.973 --> 04:35.207
[ chuckles ] why are you so
excited about a country club?

04:35.209 --> 04:37.109
Because
of "caddyshack"!

04:37.111 --> 04:40.279
It's my favorite movie --
set in a country club.

04:40.281 --> 04:42.714
I've always
wanted to go to one.
Hmm.

04:42.716 --> 04:44.283
[ chuckles ]
"spaulding, get your foot
off the boat!"

04:44.285 --> 04:45.384
[ laughs ]

04:45.386 --> 04:48.553
It's so much yelling.
It's so good.

04:48.555 --> 04:50.389
[ school bell rings ]

04:50.391 --> 04:51.890
[ indistinct shouting ]

04:54.394 --> 04:55.961
Tess is not
with nicole today.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.796
This is my chance
to sit next to her.

04:57.798 --> 04:59.264
Shut up.
You'll get us all killed.

04:59.266 --> 05:00.499
I need to show her

05:00.501 --> 05:02.601
That I'm not just a little kid
that naps on the bus,

05:02.603 --> 05:05.070
And I'm gonna do it
with this.

05:06.639 --> 05:09.274
I'm holding up
ice cube's "predator" album.

05:09.276 --> 05:11.310
"parental advisory."

05:11.312 --> 05:14.112
Once she gets I listen to badass
music, she'll know I'm down.

05:14.114 --> 05:16.281
♪ unh-unh
[ rapping ] ♪ and, no, I'm not
the butler, I'll cut ya ♪

05:16.283 --> 05:18.684
♪ headbutt ya,
you say you can't touch this ♪

05:18.686 --> 05:21.119
♪ and I wouldn't touch ya,
in fact I'll buck ya ♪

05:21.121 --> 05:23.322
♪ unh
♪ here to let you know,
boy, oh, boy ♪

05:23.324 --> 05:25.490
Feel this, girl.
♪ I'll make dough,
but don't call me doughboy ♪

05:25.492 --> 05:26.858
♪ this ain't no kind
of motion picture ♪

05:26.860 --> 05:29.261
Damn,
you're a grown-ass man.

05:29.263 --> 05:31.430
♪ I'll get...

05:31.432 --> 05:34.933
♪ check yo self
before you wreck yo self ♪

05:34.935 --> 05:36.802
♪ 'cause I'm bad
for your health ♪

05:36.804 --> 05:39.805
♪ I come real stealth,
ye-e-e-ah ♪

05:39.807 --> 05:42.274
♪ check yo self
before you wreck yo self ♪

05:42.276 --> 05:45.210
♪ chickety-check yo self
before you wreck yo self ♪

05:45.212 --> 05:46.845
♪ 'cause tricks
like you is ♪

05:46.847 --> 05:50.282
♪ b-a-a-ad for my

05:50.284 --> 05:52.451
♪ he-e-e-alth

05:52.453 --> 05:55.620
Both: ♪ hmm

05:55.622 --> 05:56.955
♪ you better

05:56.957 --> 06:02.194
[ auto-tuned ]
♪ check yo se-e-e-e-e-e-lf

06:02.196 --> 06:03.462
Yeah.

06:03.464 --> 06:05.530
Dave: Hey, did you just
fall asleep for real?

06:05.532 --> 06:07.366
You cannot
fall asleep for real.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.134
Shut up.

06:09.136 --> 06:11.403
[ sighs ]
I'm going back there.

06:11.405 --> 06:12.371
I can't watch this.

06:12.373 --> 06:16.341
♪ yeah, yeah

06:16.343 --> 06:18.610
♪ yeah, yeah

06:20.346 --> 06:23.348
How did it go?
They took my pants
and threw it out the window.

06:23.350 --> 06:26.385
♪ dig, dig,
I dig, dig, I dig ♪

06:26.387 --> 06:27.919
[ scatting ]

06:27.921 --> 06:29.388
<i>It took me forever</i>

06:29.390 --> 06:30.756
<i>To get home from school</i>
<i>that day without my pants,</i>

06:30.758 --> 06:32.190
<i>So I had</i>
<i>a lot of time to think.</i>

06:32.192 --> 06:33.992
<i>If I was gonna</i>
<i>share headphones with nicole,</i>

06:33.994 --> 06:35.560
<i>It wasn't gonna happen</i>
<i>on the bus.</i>

06:35.562 --> 06:37.562
<i>I needed</i>
<i>one-on-one time with her.</i>

06:37.564 --> 06:39.598
Thanks. See you in carpool
tomorrow, mrs. Wilson.

06:39.600 --> 06:41.600
[ car door closes ]
eddie: Carpool.

06:41.602 --> 06:45.003
Who said that?
Is someone in there?

06:45.005 --> 06:46.838
No.

06:48.741 --> 06:49.741
[ panting ]

06:49.743 --> 06:52.177
A bush kid!

06:54.447 --> 06:57.282
Which one says I am
rich enough to be invited

06:57.284 --> 06:59.751
But not rich enough that you
could ask me to donate money?

06:59.753 --> 07:02.921
I think the one with
the tokyo disney on the label.

07:02.923 --> 07:05.924
Mom, I don't want to
ride the bus anymore.

07:05.926 --> 07:07.859
I want to carpool,
and here's 50 reasons why I --

07:07.861 --> 07:10.128
Okay.
Okay?!

07:10.130 --> 07:12.397
Well, what can I say, you caught
me in a charitable mood.

07:12.399 --> 07:13.732
But not
too charitable.

07:13.734 --> 07:15.367
Yes, girl. Yes.

07:15.369 --> 07:16.568
Great!
[ chuckles ]

07:16.570 --> 07:17.903
Oh, hey.

07:17.905 --> 07:21.306
Maybe your stepdaughter nicole
would like to join?

07:21.308 --> 07:22.374
Sure.

07:22.376 --> 07:24.376
I'll ask marvin,
and then he'll ask her,

07:24.378 --> 07:26.411
And she'll tell him
what her answer is.

07:26.413 --> 07:28.580
It's like the way
we communicate at dinner.

07:28.582 --> 07:30.449
Takes a long time
to get the salt.

07:30.451 --> 07:32.951
[ exhales sharply ]
yes!

07:34.487 --> 07:36.488
That seat's taken.
Get in the back.

07:36.490 --> 07:38.523
Are you saving that seat
for your attitude?

07:40.560 --> 07:41.927
My bus friends
already miss me,

07:41.929 --> 07:43.929
So they dropped off
this breakfast burrito.

07:43.931 --> 07:45.330
So sweet.

07:45.332 --> 07:47.799
Get in the back.

07:47.801 --> 07:49.434
Dad,
why are <i>you</i> coming?

07:49.436 --> 07:52.604
Oh. I want to see the billboard
glistening in the morning dew.

07:52.606 --> 07:55.807
Okay, but don't do anything
embarrassing in front of nicole.

07:55.809 --> 07:56.975
[ high-pitched voice ]
ooh!

07:56.977 --> 07:59.611
Aah-choo-ny!

07:59.613 --> 08:01.146
[ sniffs ] oh.
Come on.

08:01.148 --> 08:03.014
[ normal voice ] what?
That's how I sneeze. [ sniffs ]

08:04.784 --> 08:07.252
Okay, get in. Let's go.
But we don't have nicole yet!

08:07.254 --> 08:08.520
Oh, she's not coming.

08:08.522 --> 08:11.156
Honey said nicole told marvin
that she's happy on the bus.

08:11.158 --> 08:13.325
But don't worry.
Your best friend, mark, is here.

08:13.327 --> 08:15.327
Hi!

08:15.329 --> 08:16.328
Who's that?

08:16.330 --> 08:17.796
I don't even know
who he is!

08:17.798 --> 08:20.799
You don't recognize me because
we always have our eyes closed,

08:20.801 --> 08:22.601
But I ride the bus
with you.

08:22.603 --> 08:25.537
So happy not to have to
do that anymore.

08:25.539 --> 08:28.006
Get in.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.007
[ van door closes ]

08:29.009 --> 08:32.444
Mark, have you ever seen
a billboard?

08:32.446 --> 08:35.013
Picture yourself
a hungry accountant

08:35.015 --> 08:37.482
Who's just taken
his kids to disney world.
Mm-hmm.

08:37.484 --> 08:39.484
♪ baby, here I am

08:39.486 --> 08:42.320
♪ I got that good love, girl,
you didn't know? ♪

08:42.322 --> 08:45.891
♪ all I need
is one more chance ♪

08:45.893 --> 08:49.661
And...The homeless man
with the dead bird

08:49.663 --> 08:52.297
Cues us to turn our heads,
look up to the sky,

08:52.299 --> 08:53.532
And -- aah!

08:56.969 --> 08:59.037
Whoa!

08:59.039 --> 09:00.839
There's chorizo
in here!

09:00.841 --> 09:02.641
Those guys.

09:05.878 --> 09:07.145
Folks, I promise,

09:07.147 --> 09:08.146
We'll get someone to clean it
as soon as we can.

09:08.148 --> 09:09.180
Nobody tried
to stop them?!

09:09.182 --> 09:10.582
Everyone
just stood around

09:10.584 --> 09:12.751
And watched my husband's
face get milked on?

09:12.753 --> 09:15.587
Nobody's gonna believe I let
a cow do that to me, right?

09:15.589 --> 09:16.655
I wouldn't worry.

09:16.657 --> 09:18.590
Probably just
random kids in the area.

09:18.592 --> 09:19.891
This is anatomically
impossible.

09:19.893 --> 09:21.593
Everybody know
you got to squeeze the teat

09:21.595 --> 09:23.228
To produce the milk.

09:23.230 --> 09:26.865
I just wish it didn't look like
I was enjoying it so much.

09:26.867 --> 09:28.600
[ horn honking ]

09:30.169 --> 09:32.370
Why won't
they hurry up?

09:32.372 --> 09:33.672
Calm your panties.

09:33.674 --> 09:35.540
You calm <i>your</i> panties!
I'm gonna be marked absent!

09:35.542 --> 09:38.376
And they'll take away
my always-there bear!

09:38.378 --> 09:40.946
All because of
your stupid carpool.

09:40.948 --> 09:42.280
Hey, I hate it, too.

09:42.282 --> 09:44.749
Guys, come on. Don't say that
about the carpool.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.384
[ sighs ]
I'm going back to the bus.
[ horn honking ]

09:46.386 --> 09:48.954
It may be hell, but at least
I get to see nicole.

09:48.956 --> 09:51.022
Well, you'll also
get to see her tonight.

09:51.024 --> 09:53.224
What?
I heard mom invite her over

09:53.226 --> 09:55.026
After she said no
to the carpool.

09:55.028 --> 09:56.628
[ exhales sharply ]

09:56.630 --> 09:59.230
Why does everyone
hate this?

09:59.232 --> 10:00.599
[ horn honks ]

10:00.601 --> 10:03.435
Why won't
they hurry up?!

10:03.437 --> 10:05.236
[ horn blares ]

10:05.238 --> 10:06.871
[ doorbell rings ]

10:06.873 --> 10:09.274
Oh, hey, girl.

10:09.276 --> 10:10.575
Didn't know you were
coming over tonight.

10:10.577 --> 10:12.777
Caught me
strengthening my hands.

10:12.779 --> 10:14.579
Wow.

10:14.581 --> 10:16.081
Everything okay?

10:16.083 --> 10:17.549
Oh, yeah. We're gonna
have a great time.

10:17.551 --> 10:19.884
Bye, sweetie.
Have fun babysitting.

10:19.886 --> 10:21.219
"babysitting"?

10:21.221 --> 10:25.624
Honey, I'm glad that you
did not wear a yellow dress

10:25.626 --> 10:27.892
Because I am wearing
a yellow dress.

10:27.894 --> 10:30.562
Well, you did call me
and say not to wear yellow --

10:30.564 --> 10:32.664
Okay, I will see you
at the country club. Bye.

10:32.666 --> 10:33.798
[ laughing ] bye.

10:33.800 --> 10:34.866
Nicole, come in.

10:36.302 --> 10:38.670
Um...

10:38.672 --> 10:40.271
[ door closes ]
...Is that old lady
self-sufficient?

10:40.273 --> 10:42.674
Because my parents showed me
"cocoon" when I was little,

10:42.676 --> 10:44.109
And I just can't.

10:44.111 --> 10:45.510
Oh, she's fine.

10:45.512 --> 10:47.445
She'll fight you for dominance
and then fall asleep.

10:47.447 --> 10:49.648
Okay.

10:49.650 --> 10:52.317
Babysitting?
Why can't grandma watch us?

10:52.319 --> 10:55.687
Because last time,
she charged me $100 an hour.

10:57.757 --> 10:59.157
All right,
we've got to get going.

10:59.159 --> 11:01.126
